This paper involves the use of reinforcement learning with neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus is on improving the learning performance of computer players in a strategy board game, which relates to game theory (cs.GT) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for an integrated game development environment, which could be related to software engineering (cs.SE) or systems and control (cs.SY).
